---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Methodology notes for the synthetic TorchLens Model Menagerie scaffold.">
  <section class="shell max-w-4xl space-y-8 py-10">
    <div>
      <p class="mono text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">Methodology</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-semibold">Every diagram starts from one line of TorchLens</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-8" style="color: var(--secondary);">The production site will render architecture diagrams from TorchLens traces, attach source and validation metadata, and publish a reproducible export. This scaffold proves the static architecture without touching real menagerie data.</p>
    </div>
    <section class="panel p-5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Credibility model</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-7" style="color: var(--secondary);">The funnel distinguishes catalog presence, build rendering, and forward validation. The synthetic counts intentionally keep real forward validation small so the UI does not overstate verification.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="panel p-5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Reproducibility</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-7" style="color: var(--secondary);">The fixture generator is deterministic, uses only the Python standard library, and writes a manifest plus checksums for generated assets. Replacing fixture/export/v1 is the intended production data seam.</p>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
